@NODE "Einf" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{i}GetSize @{ui} is a small programm, which shows information about the
Size of Files and Dircetories. @{i}GetSize@{ui} shows the Total Size of Dirs,
the Number of Files inside and the Nummer of Dirs inside.

GetSize is written specially for the Usage with the Toolmanager (Drag'n Drop),
but it also works fine from Workbench or CLI.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

To Install it is enough, to copy @{i}GetSize @{ui} in a Directory you want
and add it to the Toolmanager.It's important to enable Start from WB.
I suggest to copy GetSize into your C:-Directory.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Vor" "Systemrequirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

 · OS 2.1 (v38) +

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Use" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"

You may use GetSize together with the Toolmanager, the CLI
or the Workbench.

Start from CLI:

   @{b}GetSize <DIR>  [DIRS] [FILES] [COUNT] [TERSE] [NORECURSE] [PATTERN=pattern]@{ub}

 @{i}for example:@{ui}

   @{b}GetSize RAM:ENV@{ub}

New in V1.4 are these options:

DIRS	counts the number of subdirectories. This option is only
        useful in addition to TERSE and COUNT.

FILES   number of files.

COUNT   counts directories and files.

TERSE   only prints the "blank" number of bytes without any text. This
        is useful for ARexx scripts etc. Depending on DIRS or FILES it
		can also print the number of files or directories. Simply try
        it.

NORECURSE  doen´t enter subdirectories.

PATTERN=  here you can specify a pattern (AmigaDOS: ~,?,#? etc.) that
        is compared to every filename. Only files that matches this
		pattern are counted. Doen´t effect directories.

		
Start from Workbench:

One "click" on the GetSize-Icon and a "doubleclick" on the
directory that you want to get information about.

@ENDNODE
